Intervene.origin: [may be held liable even though other independent agencies between his negligence and the ultimate result " Hooks Superx Inc. v. McLaughlin , 642 N.E.2d 514 (1994)"]

1.definition: to occur, fall, or come between points of time or events [may be held liable even though other independent agencies between his negligence and the ultimate result ", 642 N.E.2d 514 (1994)"]

2 a.definition: to come in or between by way of hindrance or modification [ to stop a fight]

sub_terms.b: to become a party to a legal proceeding begun by others in order to protect an alleged interest in the subject matter of the proceeding [the Commissioner of Internal Revenue was granted leave to "P. A. Freund"] compare,,
